##   first use pip3 to install pyperclip module as bellow

pip3 install pyperclip

## if you get Error that says â€œPyperclip could not find a copy/paste mechanism for your system ..." Just install 'xsel' or 'xclip'  
# for example if you on fedora just enter bellow

sudo dnf install xclip


## To use it as a normal command in Linux just add it to your envirment variable and dont forget to make it Executable

chmod +x mapit.py
PATH=PATH:~/bin   ---- >  This is where you put mapit.py
